				<img loading="lazy" src="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/82/a2/18/82a2188c985ce75402ae44fc43fe7e5e.png" class="max-w-none" alt="Python">
				<img loading="lazy" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/R_logo.svg/1280px-R_logo.svg.png" class="max-w-none" alt="R">
				<img loading="lazy" src="https://play-lh.googleusercontent.com/oiIVJOsRwPWMv5FfkneTnsuN-GdB53QUH49vfKBFP0iUnlSw3I4NnxDP0w7CMgqttXQ" class="max-w-none" alt="SPSS">
				<img loading="lazy" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/New_Power_BI_Logo.svg/1024px-New_Power_BI_Logo.svg.png" class="max-w-none" alt="Power BI">
				<img loading="lazy" src="https://swimburger.net/media/ppnn3pcl/azure.png" class="max-w-none" alt="Azure">
				<img loading="lazy" src="https://tribes.agency/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/ext-550.png" class="max-w-none" alt="SQL Server">
				<img loading="lazy" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/Postgresql_elephant.svg/993px-Postgresql_elephant.svg.png" class="max-w-none" alt="PostgreSQL">
				<img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn4.iconfinder.com/data/icons/logos-and-brands/512/97_Docker_logo_logos-512.png" class="max-w-none" alt="Docker">
				<img loading="lazy" src="https://astro.js.org/astro.png" class="max-w-none" alt="Astro">
				<img loading="lazy" src="https://www.loopple.com/img/tailwind-logo.png" class="max-w-none" alt="Tailwind">
			</article>
		</section>		
		<section class="w-full lg:w-[1140px] mx-auto mt-32 z-1 projects-section" id="projects">
			<h1 class="text-center !text-5xl lg:!text-9xl mx-auto z-[-3] opacity-60 font-black section-title">PROJECTS</h1>
			<article class="flex flex-col w-full h-screen bg-[#222] mt-80 opacity-0 rounded-md overflow-hidden efinex">
				<div class="relative w-full h-full video-container">
					<video src="/videos/efinex-video.mp4" class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full object-cover" muted></video>
					<div class="
						absolute z-2 bottom-0 top-0 w-full h-full
						bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent from-40% via-black/50 to-black/80
					">
					</div>
					<div class="absolute opacity-0 top-[40%] z-10 px-3 lg:p-16 project-hover-text">
						<h2 class="!text-3xl lg:!text-6xl font-bold text-[#9d4edd] animationn">EFINEX</h2>
						<p class="mt-5 text-pretty text-base lg:!text-xl project-exp">
							This web application allows users to explore the current stock market by interacting with statistical graphs and viewing market 
							data by hovering over them. It includes indicators such as On-Balance Volume (OBV), Moving Average Convergence/Divergence (MACD), 
							Stochastic Oscillator (SO), and Accumulation/Distribution (A/D). The app offers an excellent user experience, developed with Dash and 
							Plotly APIs, and was challenging to create due to the multiple callbacks and statistical calculations involved.
						</p>

						<nav class="flex gap-x-3 mt-3">
							<Pills href="https://github.com/unfresh25/finance-dash-explorer">
								<Github class="size-5" />
								View code
							</Pills>
							<Pills href="https://finance-dash-explorer.onrender.com/">
								<Website class="size-5" />
								View website
							</Pills>
						</nav>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>
			<article class="flex flex-col w-full h-screen bg-[#222] mt-80 opacity-0 rounded-md overflow-hidden f1-dash">
				<div class="relative w-full h-full video-container">
					<video src="/videos/f1-video.mp4" class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full object-cover" muted></video>
					<div class="
						absolute z-2 bottom-0 top-0 w-full h-full
						bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent from-10% via-black/50 to-black/80
					">
					</div>
					<div class="absolute opacity-0 top-[40%] z-10 px-3 lg:p-16 project-hover-text">
						<h2 class="!text-3xl lg:!text-6xl font-bold text-[#9d4edd] animationn">F1 Dashboard</h2>
						<p class="mt-5 text-pretty text-base lg:!text-xl project-exp">
							The application is designed to provide a comprehensive overview of Formula 1 racing data, including race results, driver performance, and circuit 
							information. The user can explore and analyze the data in various ways to gain insights into the drivers, races, and circuits of the world's most 
							prestigious Formula 1 racing organization.
						</p>

						<nav class="flex gap-x-3 mt-3">
							<Pills href="https://github.com/unfresh25/finance-dash-explorer">
								<Github class="size-5" />
								View code
							</Pills>
							<Pills href="https://finance-dash-explorer.onrender.com/">
								<Website class="size-5" />
